					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On January 09, 2006 at 06:57 AM, Michael Chu said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Anonymous wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>Is black vanilla beans ok? How long and where can you store the vanilla beans?</div></div><br />
Are there non-black vanilla beans? I believe that all vanilla bean pods turn dark brown or black when dried and matured.<br />
<br />
Vanilla beans should be able to be stored indefinitely when properly stored. Keep them in a cool dry place in an airtight container. Don't store them in the refrigerator or the freezer. I've heard of many people storing them in vodka or covering them in sugar with great success. The vodka and sugar then becomes vanilla flavored after a few weeks.</div>
