					<div class="commentbody">While I have successfully caramelized the sugar under the broiler, I got much more even and professional-looking results with a propane torch. Just get a "basic use" propane soldering kit (such as the Bernzomatic UL100 -- which works fabuluously, even upside down) at your friendly megamart for right around $12. Skip on the tiny butane toy-torches - they cost almost as much, have a very narrow flame and demand continuous refilling.</div>
