					<div class="commentheading">On March 23, 2007 at 06:37 PM, Jeff_Lin said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">To answer the scalding milk question, scalded milk helps melt the sugar and give everything a head start, in addition to accentuating whatever flavors you've decided to add. Another reason you use scalded milk is the same reason you use *boiling* water for the water bath; a "jump" is required to make sure the creme brulee cooks evenly and thoroughly.</div>
