I can't help but think we're not communicating correctly here. I'm asking if it's temperature or spiciness. It's not clear to me if you are using hot and burning to represent temperature or a sensation. Both should be impossible with creme brulee - if it's too hot (temperature), refrigerate it for an hour after using the torch. If it's too hot (spiciness), check your ingredients (maybe buy new ones) - maybe something went bad - although I can't imagine how cream, eggs, and sugar could be spicy. Hmmm... vanilla sugar. Taste that on it's own - maybe it's vanilla chili sugar (vanilla and chili powder is a combination that you could find in Central and South American cuisine).</div>
