					<div class="commentheading">On December 14, 2007 at 10:09 PM, Dilbert said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Scripty -<br />
<br />
"over cooking" custard dishes pi's to omegas - is the usual cause for cracking.<br />
<br />
it's a high wire act - <br />
undercooked = gooey centers<br />
overcooked = cracks<br />
<br />
did you do these in a water bath?<br />
the temperature inertia of a water bath should give you a bit more leeway (clock time) in checking / pulling from oven.</div>
					<hr size="1" noshade />
				
					<hr size="1" noshade />
					<div class="commentheading">On December 14, 2007 at 10:14 PM, Scripty (guest) said...</div>
