					<div class="commentheading">On December 15, 2007 at 01:06 PM, Dilbert said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">custards being an egg dish, I wouldn't recycle them.<br />
<br />
if they are still too loose in the middles, but parts(?) have cracked, and you used a water bath, I'm suspecting the oven temp was too high and would recommend you use a separate thermometer to double check.<br />
<br />
the theory behind the water bath is to allow then entire mass to all come up to temperature in an even way.</div>
