					<div class="commentheading">On December 20, 2007 at 07:14 PM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>no torch...no problem</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">Most ovens have a broiler, use that if you don't have a torch.  It's best to place the creme brulee closest to the flame/ high-heat-distribution-unit after having put the sugar on top--just make sure not to burn the sugar.  Keep in mind that once sugar boils, it'll harden when cooled.  If you want the look of the torch, you need to pay very close attention to burning the sugar otherwise you can ruin the creme.   B)</div>
