					<div class="commentheading">On July 04, 2011 at 07:22 PM, yocona said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Re: re:film ontop of brulee</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>Alana wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>you need to put glad wrap/cling wrap on top of your custard before placing it in the fridge this should stop a skin from forming</div></div>This technique is great for preventing a skin from forming on unbaked custard.  When I read KEBAK's post, I assumed s/he was referring to custard that had been baked.  I've never had a skin form on the baked custard.  What I have experienced is more like a layer of fat that separated from the rest of the custard, and then became solid once the brulees were chilled.</div>
