					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">creme brulee is at basis an egg custard with an eye appealing sugar 'top'<br />
<br />
the custard really does not have a lot of marked flavors so it lends itself to being "spiced up"<br />
<br />
a bit of googling will turn up all kinds of flavorings - including both white pepper and cayenne.<br />
<br />
I think the combo works because the pepper has a little "bite" to it which offsets the sweet/creamy nature of the custard.<br />
<br />
if you want to try it, I can only offer this advice:  a little cayenne goes a long way - it's easily overdone.</div>
